                <section id="getting-started">
                    <h2>Getting Started</h2>
                    
                    <h3 id="overview">Overview</h3>
                    <p>The Arrow API is a comprehensive RESTful API that provides access to Roblox data including user profiles, group membership, games, social connections, and more. It's designed to be simple, fast, and reliable for developers who need to integrate Roblox data into their applications.</p>

                    <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <strong>üöÄ What's New:</strong> We've expanded beyond group membership! Explore our new <a href="/docs/roblox/user-profile">User Profile APIs</a>, <a href="/docs/roblox/social/friends">Social APIs</a>, and more in the sidebar.
                    </div>

                    <h3 id="authentication">Authentication</h3>
                    <p>All API requests require authentication using an API key. You can generate API keys from your <a href="/dashboard">dashboard</a> after logging in with Discord.</p>
                    
                    <div class="alert alert-warning">
                        <strong>Security Notice:</strong> Keep your API keys secure and never expose them in client-side code. Use environment variables or secure storage.
                    </div>

                    <h4>How to Authenticate</h4>
                    <p>Include your API key in the request headers for every API call:</p>
                    <div class="code-block">
                        <pre><code>api-key: your-api-key-here</code></pre>
                    </div>

                    <h4>Getting Your API Key</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Visit the <a href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a></li>
                        <li>Log in with your Discord account</li>
                        <li>Generate a new API key</li>
                        <li>Copy and use it in your requests</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3 id="base-url">Base URL</h3>
                    <p>All API endpoints use the following base URL:</p>
                    <div class="code-block">
                        <pre><code>https://arrow-api.up.railway.app</code></pre>
                    </div>

                    <h3 id="quick-start">Quick Start Example</h3>
                    <p>Here's a simple example to check if a user is in a group:</p>
                    <div class="code-block">
                        <pre><code>curl -X GET "https://arrow-api.up.railway.app/1/1" \
  -H "api-key: your-api-key-here"</code></pre>
                    </div>

